title.narrative: 1.17 NEWBORN CARE SERVICES

description.narrative: Government and partners have capacity to scale up improved service delivery at community and facility level sanitation and hygiene especially for the most deprived communities, which contributes to Adolescent Health And Nutrition, Child Health, Hiv Prevention, Maternal And Newborn Health, Pmtct And Infant Male Circumcision. UNICEF aims to achieve this through Advocacy And Public Engagement, Developing And Leveraging Resources And Partnerships, Evaluations, Research And Data, Fostering Innovation And Use Of New Technologies, Operational Support To Programme Delivery, Systems Strengthening And Institution Building. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: Programme Component Results (PCR) 1: Mother and child survival, growth and development

description.narrative: Scale up of interventions delivered around birth accelerated focussing on: equity, quality, convergence and monitoring. 67.3% of high priority districts have model labour rooms, 75% have Special Newborn Care Units (SNCUs) with monitoring systems expanded to 77 more SNCUs, integrating community follow up linking facility and community care. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:14/01/2018
